@page "/privacy"
@using MudBlazor

<PageTitle>Privacy Policy – Cyclone</PageTitle>

<MudContainer Class="mt-6 mb-6">
  <MudPaper Elevation="1" Class="p-6 legal-card">

    <MudText Typo="Typo.h4" GutterBottom>Privacy Policy</MudText>

    <MudText Typo="Typo.subtitle2" Class="mt-4">1. Controller</MudText>
    <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-3">
      The data controller within the meaning of data protection laws is Cyclone GmbH, Musterstraße 1, 12345 Musterstadt,
      Email: datenschutz@cyclone.com, Phone: +49 123 456789.
    </MudText>

    <MudText Typo="Typo.subtitle2" Class="mt-4">2. Collection and Storage of Personal Data</MudText>
    <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-3">
      (1) When visiting our website, the following data is automatically collected: IP address, browser type,
      date and time of access, and visited pages. Processing is based on Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR for the operation and security of the site. <br />
      (2) We also collect data that you voluntarily provide during registration or ordering (name, address, payment details).
    </MudText>

    <MudText Typo="Typo.subtitle2" Class="mt-4">3. Purposes of Data Processing</MudText>
    <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-3">
      We use your data • for contract execution, • for payment processing, • for shipping, • for customer service requests,
      and • for marketing emails (only with your consent).
    </MudText>

    <MudText Typo="Typo.subtitle2" Class="mt-4">4. Disclosure to Third Parties</MudText>
    <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-3">
      Your data will only be shared with • shipping service providers (purpose: delivery), • payment service providers
      (purpose: payment processing), and • other service providers acting on our behalf (Art. 28 GDPR).
    </MudText>

    <MudText Typo="Typo.subtitle2" Class="mt-4">5. Cookies & Tracking</MudText>
    <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-3">
      We use session cookies for cart functionality and technically necessary features.
      Analytics cookies (e.g., Google Analytics) are only used with your consent according to Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR.
    </MudText>

    <MudText Typo="Typo.subtitle2" Class="mt-4">6. Data Subject Rights</MudText>
    <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-3">
      You have the right to access, rectification, deletion, restriction, and objection (Art. 15–21 GDPR).
      To exercise these rights, please contact us via email at datenschutz@cyclone.com.
    </MudText>

    <MudText Typo="Typo.subtitle2" Class="mt-4">7. Data Security</MudText>
    <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-3">
      We use TLS encryption (https) for all data transmissions. Within our systems, your data is protected
      by organizational, technical, and physical measures.
    </MudText>

    <MudText Typo="Typo.subtitle2" Class="mt-4">8. Changes to This Policy</MudText>
    <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-3">
      We may update this Privacy Policy as necessary. The current version is always available at
      https://www.cyclone.com/privacy.
    </MudText>

    <MudText Typo="Typo.caption" Align="Align.Center" Class="mt-6">
      Last updated: August 2025
    </MudText>

  </MudPaper>
</MudContainer>
